[[Image:Misfits8.jpg|thumb|180px|right|[[Jerry Only]] sporting a Devilock in concert.]]
The '''devilock''' is a [[hairstyle]] created by [[Misfits (band)|Misfits]] bassist [[Jerry Only]] in the late 1970s.<ref>{{cite book |title= Hair Designing: A Complete Course |year= 2007 |publisher= Global Media |isbn= 978-81-89940-59-1 |page= 97 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=AGiUuD_N1d0C&pg=PT97 |accessdate=2009-12-08}}</ref> In an early 1980s interview, Only claimed that the devilock was based on a "tidal wave" hairstyle seen among the 1970s [[skateboarding]] communities. In the same interview, former Misfits vocalist [[Glenn Danzig]] explains that his version of the hairstyle developed from an imitation of [[Eddie Munster]]'s hairstyle. A style similar to the Devilock was sported earlier - for instance the Surfari's cover picture of 'Gum-dipped Slicks' (1964) shows a member of the band with a devilock-like quiff <ref>https://sundazed.com/c/365-Original-Surfaris-The.aspx</ref>.
In a devilock, the sides and back of the hair are kept short, while the front is kept long and combed forward.<ref>{{cite book |title= The Official Punk Rock Book of Lists |last= Wallace |first= Amy |last2= Manitoba |first2= Richard |year= 2007 |publisher= Hal Leonard Corporation |isbn= 978-0-87930-919-0 |page= 131 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=HFKSxVpoPbMC&pg=PA131 |accessdate= 2009-12-08}}</ref> In the late 1990s, the devilock experienced a resurgence of popularity in Asian markets that saw the hairstyle spread from punk rock to mainstream culture. Following popularization in Japanese and Chinese rock groups, the hairstyle's name was appropriated by Noriaki Endo in his chain of retail clothing stores.<ref>{{cite interview|interviewer=Jeremy Goh|subject=Noriaki Endo|title=Feature Interview With Endo – DEVILOCK|url=http://www.plussixfive.com/2009/10/30/feature-interview-with-endo-devilock/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091101151708/http://www.plussixfive.com/2009/10/30/feature-interview-with-endo-devilock/|date=October 30, 2009|archivedate=November 1, 2009|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite interview|interviewer1=Thomas Bradley |interviewer2=Debre|subject=Noriaki Endo|editor=Poe|date=March 23, 2006|title=Freshness Feature: Noriaki Endo – Devilock Founder|url=http://www.freshnessmag.com/2006/03/23/interview-with-noriaki-endo-founder-of-devilock/}}</ref> The "Devilock" brand currently sponsors music events called "Devilock Nights" throughout Southeast Asia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.devilock.com/english/history/|title=History of Devilock|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130101080119/http://devilock.com/english/history/|archivedate= January 1, 2013|deadurl=yes}}</ref>
